crossing /ˈkrɒsɪŋ/

(crossings) 

1. N-COUNT A crossing is a journey by boat or ship to a place on the other side of an ocean, river, or lake. 横渡 

例： He made the crossing from Cape Town to Sydney in just over twenty-six days. 他从开普敦横渡到悉尼只用了二十六天多时间。 

2. N-COUNT A crossing is a place where two roads, paths, or lines cross. 交叉路口 

例： She sighed and squatted down next to the crossing of the two trails. 她叹了口气，在两条小路的交叉口旁蹲了下来。 

3. N-COUNT A crossing is the same as a  or a . 平交道口

